// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/parse/notes/n14/fail-malformed.test — N14 (lang.ebnf:1113)
// malformed `#line` directive locked-text diagnostic.
//
// Per spec.md FR-027 + tasks.md T041: a `#line` directive whose
// argument is NOT a positive integer (e.g., `#line abc`) MUST emit
// the LOCKED diagnostic text:
//
//   '#line' directive must be followed by a positive integer (parser-note N14)
//
// The grammar (`lang.ebnf §2` line 107):
//
//   line_marker = "#line" decimal_integer [ string_literal ] ;
//
// requires a `decimal_integer` between `#line` and the optional
// string. A non-integer there is a syntax error; M1 may emit the
// directive verbatim through the seam (variant 3 textual form), in
// which case the parser sees the malformed shape and is responsible
// for the diagnostic — that's the assertion below.
//
// Per the contract (`nslc-emit-ast.contract.md` §"Behavior"), an
// error-severity diagnostic at parse time means exit 1 and NO AST
// on stdout. We use `not %nslc` to assert non-zero exit and a
// `--check-prefix=FAIL` to namespace the assertion against any
// stderr noise from M1 layers.
//
// FR-029 RED state: at 7bc1aea, no `-emit=ast` flag; the driver
// returns exit 2 (argument error), not exit 1 (parse error), AND
// the locked-text diagnostic is never emitted because there is no
// `nsl-parse` library to emit it. Principle VIII evidence.

// RUN: not %nslc -emit=ast %s 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=FAIL

#line abc
module n14_fail {
    wire q;
}

// FR-027 locked-string assertion. The text MUST appear EXACTLY as
// written; any drift is a constitutional finding (Principle VIII
// "diagnostic-bearing rules test the diagnostic text") and a Track
// D coordination event.
// FAIL: error: '#line' directive must be followed by a positive integer (parser-note N14)
